This paper discusses adversarial attacks and defenses in machine learning, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper proposes a method for constructing adversarial examples that can defeat two recently proposed defenses, which suggests a focus on adversarial attacks and defenses in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV and cs.CR. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks as the basis for their experiments, which suggests a possible fit for the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
